[Method]
GetColorValue
[Prefix]
dcl_
[Desc]
This function converts an AutoCAD, system, or (Red Green Blue) color value into an OLE color suitable for use with an ActiveX control or OLE object.
[Arguments Return] as Long
<CONTROL>
\par\tab Color
[as Integer or (R G B)]


[Method]
GetOleObject
[Prefix]
dcl_AxControl_
[Desc]
Returns the OLE object handle for this control. When finished using the handle, call \cf2dcl_AxObject_Close \cf0 to release it from memory.
[Arguments Return] as Handle
<CONTROL>


GetProperty
[Prefix]
dcl_AxControl_
[Desc]
Gets the value of any property of an OLE object. The type of the return value will depend on the type of the property.
[Arguments Return] as Varied
<CONTROL>
\par\tab PropName
[as String]


SetColorProperty
[Prefix]
dcl_AxControl_
[Desc]
Returns the value of a color property. The result is automatically converted into an OpenDCL color value.
[Arguments Return] as Varied
<CONTROL>
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 PropName (default: "Color")
[as String]
\par\tab Color
[as Integer or (R G B)]


SetPictureProperty
[Prefix]
dcl_AxControl_
[Desc]
Returns the value of a color property. The result is automatically converted into an OpenDCL color value.
[Arguments Return] as Varied
<CONTROL>
\par\tab \i{Optional} \i0 PropName (default: "Picture")
[as String]
\par\tab PictureID
[as Integer]


SetProperty
[Prefix]
dcl_AxControl_
[Desc]
Sets the value of any property of an OLE object. The type of the argument should match (or be convertable to) the type of the property.
[Arguments Return] as Varied
<CONTROL>
\par\tab PropName
[as String]
\par \tab ...


DoMethod
[Prefix]
dcl_AxControl_
[Desc]
Calls any method of an OLE object. The type of the arguments should match (or be convertable to) the argument types of the method.
[Arguments Return] as Varied
<CONTROL>
\par\tab MethodName
[as String]
\par \tab ...


[End of File]
